commentTextItems.html: full toss, Bashar steps out and drives to mid-on, single taken

commentPostTextItems.html: Bangladesh have done it in style rocking home by 6 wickets. Openers came out good with each one knocking a half-century. Nafees continued his good form with the bat making a quickfire 67 runs off 68 balls with Mehrab playing the supporting role and coming up with his maiden fifty. Saqibul and Bashar finished off in style with some good blows taking Bangladesh home in a comfortable manner. Please join us for the 3rd ODI to be played at the same stadium on Dec 5. Cheers and Bye!

stories.title: 'We enjoyed the batting' - Mehrab
stories.subTitle: Bangladesh v Zimbabwe, 2nd ODI, Bogra
stories.summary: Mehrab Hossain jr, one half of Bangladesh's newest opening pair, is confident of his rapport with Shahriar Nafees

stories.title: Nafees and Mehrab set up easy win
stories.subTitle: Bangladesh v Zimbabwe, 2nd ODI, Bogra
stories.seoTitle: Nafees and Mehrab set up easy win
stories.summary: A flamboyant half-century from Shahriar Nafees plus a more sedate contribution from Mehrab Hossain guided Bangladesh to a comfortable six-wicket victory over Zimbabwe, in the second one-day international at Bogra, and a 2-0 series lead
